  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To paint tiles on a map using a tile group, you call "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sktilemapnode/1643615-fillwithtilegroup"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " on the group. The fill behaviors you use depend on the type of group you make: "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "table",
          "header": "row",
          "rows": [
            [
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Group type"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Fill behavior"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Single tile"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Repeats the single center tile."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Multiple tiles without adjacency rules"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Chooses randomly among the multiple center tiles, abiding by the placement weights you choose."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Multiple tiles with adjacency rules"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Repeats the center tile and borders all of its edges using the peripheral adjacency tiles you define."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            ]
          ],
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "3111469",
            "title": "Table 1"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Create a Tile Group with a Single Tile",
          "anchor": "3111467"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Although a tile group is a container for multiple tiles, you can create one with a single tile, if you wish. Use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sktilegroup/1643832-initwithtiledefinition"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " initializer, as shown in the following code.  "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "let backgroundTexture = SKTexture(imageNamed: \"BG.png\")",
            "let backgroundDefinition = SKTileDefinition(texture: backgroundTexture)",
            "let backgroundGroup = SKTileGroup(tileDefinition: backgroundDefinition)"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "3111468",
            "title": "Listing 1"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Create a Heterogenous Tile Group with Random Placement",
          "anchor": "3111456"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For a tile group with more than one texture, use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sktilegroup/1643839-initwithrules"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " initializer. The following code shows how you can create a tile group containing two definitions—one based on an image named "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "RED.png"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and the other on an image named "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "BLUE.png"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [],
          "syntax": null,
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "3111461",
            "title": "Listing 2"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When a tile map node is supplied with a tile set using this group and its tiles are filled with the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sktilemapnode/1643615-fillwithtilegroup"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method, the placement weights control the random assignment of tiles. In this case, there are three times more red than blue tiles."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Create a Tile Group Using Adjacency Rules",
          "anchor": "3111453"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To create a tile group that uses adjacency, you need to create a set of rules for each of the adjacency values. For a grid-based layout, you need 13 rules, as shown in the following illustration:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-3111454",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "3111454",
                "title": "Figure 1"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To create the tile group programmatically, create definitions and rules for each adjacency:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [],
          "syntax": null,
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "3111462",
            "title": "Listing 3"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The 13 rules are used to make a tile group:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "let group = SKTileGroup(rules: [centerRule, upEdgeRule, downEdgeRule, ...]"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "3111460",
            "title": "Listing 4"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "With automapping enabled, when an individual tile is placed on the map using  "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sktilemapnode/1643605-settilegroup"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", SpriteKit also sets the tile definitions for the surrounding tiles based on the group's adjacency rules."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        }
      ]
    }
